# Phase 3.1.1 Telegram Stabilization Patch Plan

This plan details the implementation strategy to stabilize the Telegram Bot integration across different environments, eliminating ETELEGRAM 409 conflict noise and preventing background polling loops from hanging test runners or development workflows.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Environment Variables Update:**
> This patch introduces `ENABLE_TELEGRAM_BOT` to selectively enable the Telegram client. During development and testing, this should be kept as `false` or set to `true` with polling disabled to avoid network polling conflicts on the same bot token.

